1.	Do not modify the folder structure under apps/web, server, or packages unless explicitly instructed.
2.	Do not move logic between client, server, or shared packages unless the request explicitly specifies relocation.
3.	Always maintain compatibility with:
o	Firebase Auth (client)
o	Firestore access rules
o	Vercel deployment for apps/web
o	Render deployment for server
o	MCP protocol
o	Prisma schema and migrations
4.	Do not modify schema.prisma without explicitly requested instructions.
5.	Do not modify API routes without validating:
o	Authentication requirements
o	Organization scope (orgId)
o	Data ownership rules
6.	Never generate new Firebase functions unless asked.
7.	Never introduce new npm dependencies without explicit instruction.
8.	When editing React components, preserve RTL logic and existing UI patterns.
9.	When editing server logic, maintain SSE streaming compatibility.
10.	Ensure TypeScript types remain synchronized across packages.
11.	When creating new components, place them in the correct domain folder (UI / core / features).
12.	All generated code must support long-term maintainability for a monorepo environment.